    <item>
      <title>Valentine’s Interactive Hanky</title>
      <link>https://yoursite.com/systems/2014-02-13-valentines-interactive-hanky/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 13 Feb 2014 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://yoursite.com/systems/2014-02-13-valentines-interactive-hanky/</guid>
      <description>&lt;div style=&#34;position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden;&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;iframe allow=&#34;accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share; fullscreen&#34; loading=&#34;eager&#34; referrerpolicy=&#34;strict-origin-when-cross-origin&#34; src=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/embed/tAVrpWRQsZc?autoplay=0&amp;amp;controls=1&amp;amp;end=0&amp;amp;loop=0&amp;amp;mute=0&amp;amp;start=0&#34; style=&#34;position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; border:0;&#34; title=&#34;YouTube video&#34;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;It all started with the idea of creating a workshop around the theme of paper circuits, with great inspiration from the work and research of &lt;a href=&#34;https://vimeo.com/user1892233&#34;&gt;Jie Qui&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;http://lizastark.com/portfolio/paper-circuits/&#34;&gt;Liza Stark&lt;/a&gt; and others. Above all, the main idea was to transfer skills and knowledge to the team at &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.casadoconhecimento.pt/&#34;&gt;Casa do Conhecimento&lt;/a&gt;. To show how easy it is to create simple things that are both beautiful and can have a great impact. We had this initial idea but we were still lacking a concept on the same level to the technology. The workshop was planned for February, which coincided with the &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.namorarportugal.pt/&#34;&gt;Namorar Portugal&lt;/a&gt; (Flirting Portugal) event and all the Valentine happenings, and being Vila Verde the capital of this event we decided to combine the paper circuits workshop with the famous and acclaimed Lenço dos Namorados (Valentine’s handkerchief).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
